def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index
    levels = index.levels
    names = index.names

    cloc_numbers = [index.get_loc(level) for level in clocs]

    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in cloc_numbers]

    if len(rlocs) == 0:
        # Everything is in clocs, so the dummy df has a regular index
        dummy_index = pd.Index(index.get_level_values(cloc_numbers[0]), name="__placeholder__")
    else:
        dummy_index = pd.MultiIndex.from_arrays([index.get_level_values(i) for i in rlocs] + [index.get_level_values(cloc_numbers[0])],
                                               names=[names[i] for i in rlocs] + ["__placeholder__"])

    if isinstance(data, pd.Series):
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index

        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)
    else:
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index

        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)
        if isinstance(unstacked, pd.Series):
            unstcols = unstacked.index
        else:
            unstcols = unstacked.columns

    new_levels = [levels[i] for i in cloc_numbers] + [unstcols.levels[0]]
    new_names = [names[i] for i in cloc_numbers] + [data.columns.name]
    new_codes = [unstcols.codes[i] for i in range(len(cloc_numbers))] + [unstcols.codes[-1]]

    new_columns = pd.MultiIndex(levels=new_levels, codes=new_codes, names=new_names, verify_integrity=False)

    if isinstance(unstacked, pd.Series):
        unstacked.index = new_columns
    else:
        unstacked.columns = new_columns

    return unstacked
